cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper deals with the problem of clothing parsing using fully-convolutional neural networks (FCN) and extends the architecture with a side-branch network and conditional random field (CRF). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the empirical results and the qualitative influence of annotation on the current clothing parsing benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the usefulness of the image representation of the outfit encoder for dress-up image retrieval application, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper uses a Web-based tool for multi-scale pixel-wise annotation and manual refinement effort, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
